===Noun===
{{en-noun|~}}

# {{lb|en|physics}} The emission of [[electron]]s from a [[metal]] or [[semiconductor]], under the [[influence]] of a strong [[electric field]], by [[quantum tunnelling]].
#* {{quote-book|en|title=Understanding Carbon Nanotubes: From Basics to Applications|author=Annick Loiseau|year=2006|passage='''Field emission''' was described for the first time at the end of the 19th century. Thorough experiments in the 1920s showed clearly that this emission occurred under high electric field and was not related to thermoelectronic emission.|url=https://books.google.com/books?id=qNaOj0G_GcwC&lpg=PA248&dq=%22field%20emission%22&pg=PA248#v=onepage&q=%22field%20emission%22&f=false}}

====Synonyms====
* {{l|en|field electron emission}}

